{
  "texts": [
    "[310] finds the number of broken generators to be 16-ν 2 -C 2, while ρ is a full rank matrix.",
    "This gives a total number of 16-ν 2 -C 2 2Goldstone modes, all of which are quadratic.",
    "Once we move away from the chiral-flat limit, some of the Goldstone modes will become gapped at the scale of terms that break U (4)×U (4) down to U (2) × U (2) (i.e., they are pseudo-Goldstone modes 69) of the BM symmetries, while the remaining gapless modes do not necessarily remain quadratic in the U (2) × U (2) theory.We can use the same approach as above, but now with only U (2) × U (2) symmetry, to calculate the number and type of the Goldstone modes at this new scale.",
    "Since the details are state and filling-dependent, we illustrate this with a single example, that of the KIVC state at ν = 0.For the spinless model, according to Eq. 99, KIVC is captured by the order parameter Q = σ y τ x,y.",
    "Here, τ z is the only broken generator, leading to 1 linear Goldstone mode."
  ]
}